{"title":"Ring of adornment","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Ring_of_adornment","type":"markdown","data":"| =          |                                                               |   |   |\n| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- | - | - |\n| Name       | adornment                                                     |   |   |\n| Appearance | [random](/wiki/Randomised_appearance \"Randomised appearance\") |   |   |\n| Base price | 100 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\")                             |   |   |\n| Weight     | 3                                                             |   |   |\n\nWearing a **ring of adornment** modifies [charisma](/wiki/Charisma \"Charisma\").\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Identification](#Identification)\n- [2 Effects](#Effects)\n- [3 History](#History)\n- [4 Strategy](#Strategy)\n\n## Identification\n\nDropping a ring of adornment into a [sink](/wiki/Sink \"Sink\") produces the message, \"The faucets flash brightly for a moment.\"\n\n## Effects\n\nThe change in charisma is equal to the ring's [enchantment](/wiki/Enchantment \"Enchantment\"); the enchantment can be altered by [charging](/wiki/Charging \"Charging\").\n\n[Succubi](/wiki/Succubus \"Succubus\") will steal or ask for rings of adornment (\"That \\<ring> looks pretty. May I have it?\" or \"The succubus decides she'd like your \\<ring>, and takes it.\"). [Incubi](/wiki/Incubus \"Incubus\") will ask you to put on a ring of adornment if you're carrying one (\"That \\<ring> looks pretty. Would you wear it for me?\" or \"The incubus decides you'd look prettier wearing your \\<ring>, and puts it on your finger.\"). This happens regardless of the enchantment (positive, negative, or zero) on the ring. Additionally, the ring will be identified.\n\n## History\n\nIn the original [Rogue](/wiki/Rogue_\\(game\\) \"Rogue (game)\"), a ring of adornment was usually [cursed](/wiki/Cursed \"Cursed\") as it did nothing but take up ring space and cause [ring hunger](/wiki/Ring_hunger \"Ring hunger\"). Similarly, for [earlier versions of NetHack](/wiki/Game_history \"Game history\"), rings of adornment had no effect.\n\n## Strategy\n\nDon't keep unidentified rings on your inventory, or an Incubus might make you wear a cursed one with negative enchantment.\n\nOutside of improving foocubi encounter results and lowering shop prices, this ring is relatively useless and an excellent candidate for polypiling.\n\n[![This article may require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/b/b0/Nh343-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article may require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n\n**This page may need to be updated for the [current version](/wiki/Current_version \"Current version\") of *NetHack*.**\n\nIt may contain text specific to [NetHack 3.4.3](/wiki/NetHack_3.4.3 \"NetHack 3.4.3\"). Information on this page may be out of date.\n\n**Editors:** After reviewing this page and making necessary edits, please change the {{nethack-343}} tag to the current version's tag or {{noversion}} as appropriate.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Ring of adornment - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Ring_of_adornment\",\"wgTitle\":\"Ring of adornment\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":130527,\"wgRevisionId\":130527,\"wgArticleId\":1538,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Rings\",\"Nethack-343 articles\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\